        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 7 at 3:49PM MDT until September 7 at 4:15PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>SVRGJT

The National Weather Service in Grand Junction has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
West central Garfield County in west central Colorado...
Southeastern Uintah County in northeastern Utah...

* Until 415 PM MDT.

* At 349 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 37 miles northwest
of Fruita, or 46 miles northwest of Grand Junction, moving east at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
west central Garfield and southeastern Uintah Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will send your report to the National Weather Service
office in Grand Junction.</instruction>
